---
title: "Assessing the utility of a novel cortical marker of delay discounting (C-DD) in two independent samples of early adolescents: Links with externalizing pathology"
collection: publications
category: manuscripts
excerpt: 'This study finds that parent anxiety sensitivity is associated with their adolescent's brain activation in key emotion-regulation regions (like the OFC and ACC) during an fMRI task, with different patterns emerging when adolescents were asked to react versus regulate their emotions.'
date: 2023-09-26
venue: 'PLoS One'
paperurl: 'https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37756262/'
citation: 'Bounoua N, Church LD, Matyi MA, Rudoler J, Wieand K, Spielberg JM. (2023). &quot;Assessing the utility of a novel cortical marker of delay discounting (C-DD) in two independent samples of early adolescents: Links with externalizing pathology.&quot; <i>PLoS One</i>. 18(9):e0291868.'
